{
  "doc_id": "54824",
  "text": "There is another group of study focusing on recovering keystrokes on physical or virtual keyboards via acoustics. Cai et al. [CITATION_1] surveyed potential attacks using microphones. Asonov et al. [CITATION_2] present an acoustic attack to classify key presses on a physical keyboard. Zhuang et al. [CITATION_3] further improved this work. Berger et al. [CITATION_4] present a dictionary attack based on keyboard acoustic emanations. Compagno et al. [CITATION_5] infer text typed on a keyboard through the acoustic signal captured via Skype chat. Liu et al. [CITATION_6] use two microphones on a smartphone to inference presses on a keyboard. Narain et al. [CITATION_7] use a gyroscope and microphones on a mobile phone to predict keystrokes on the virtual keyboard.",
